The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Flight disruptions continued at the city airport on Monday because of heavy fog in Delhi. A SpiceJet flight from Calcutta, which had taken off on Sunday night, was unable to land in Delhi and returned to the city around 3am on Monday. An Air India flight also returned from Delhi at 4.30am because of fog. On Monday morning, JetLite had to cancel its flight to Port Blair because of shortage of aircraft caused by the fog, airport officials said. Compounding the problems for fliers, the public address system and the flight information board at the airport did not work from 3pm to 5pm. The airport authorities blamed glitches for the problems.    A postgraduate trainee at SSKM Hospital allegedly tried to rape a woman on the hospital premises on Saturday afternoon. He has been absconding since. A case was started against him on Monday.  he woman, in her late 20s, is a resident of Sandeshkhali in North 24-Parganas. Her daughter has been undergoing treatment in the orthopaedic department of the hospital since December 6. Congress and Trinamul Congress supporters demonstrated in the hospital on Monday demanding the immediate arrest of the doctor.     Three persons were injured in road mishaps on Monday. Shekhar Halder, in his early 60s, fell off a private bus on Taratala Road. The Thakurpukur resident was admitted to CMRI with a fracture in his left leg. Arjun Doghad, a 50-year-old resident of Mahestala, was hit by a private bus plying on route No. 13 at the Eden Hospital Road-College Street crossing. He was admitted to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital with multiple injuries. A private bus plying on route No. SD 18 knocked down an unidentified man in his early 30s at the intersection of Diamond Harbour Road and Judges Court Road. He was admitted to SSKM Hospital.    Saurav Santra, 19, a first-year BCom student of Prabhu Jagatbandhu College in Andul, was sent to judicial custody for 14 days on Monday. He had been arrested for allegedly beating to death Swapan Koley, 20, a second-year BCom student of the college, on December 16 during a clash between supporters of the SFI and the Trinamul Chhatra Parishad.    Employees of the Baguiati branch of Indian Overseas Bank on Monday morning noticed marks on the outer wall suggesting a gang had tried to bore a hole through the wall to access the vault. The gang damaged the security cameras positioned outside the bank to ensure that they were not filmed.     Playwright-actor-director Ramaprasad Banik died at a private hospital in the city on Monday night. He was 56. Banik was admitted to the hospital with pneumonia three days ago. He is survived by his mother, wife and two daughters.                                                                                                                                                  
